A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Absentee Ballots – Signature Requirements and Verification
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a local board of elections from removing an absentee ballot
4 from a return envelope or ballot/return envelope or counting the ballot unless the
5 return envelope or ballot/return envelope is signed by the voter and, except under
6 certain circumstances, a witness and the local board verify the voter’s signature; and
7 generally relating to absentee ballots.
